# No Legacy / No Migration Default

## 1) Default stance
- No legacy compatibility paths.
- No migration layers/adapters/shims by default.
- No dual-write/dual-read for old and new schemas unless explicitly requested.

## 2) If migration appears necessary
- Stop and ask for explicit approval.
- Default answer remains: no migration, keep code clean and minimal.
- Prefer one clean replacement path over phased compatibility logic.

## 3) Implementation implications
- Remove obsolete code instead of preserving it for backward compatibility.
- Reject API/type/storage additions that exist only for legacy support.
- Keep domain model and naming aligned to current DP-1 contract only.
